            <h1 class="mf-title">For Change Agents</h1>
            <p class="mf-subtitle mf-copy">If you’re committed to helping your school, district, or statemove forward, you’re our kind of person -- a change agent. We view our role in education as helping make our country’s education change agents more productive, and to help them
                find each other</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="copy-container moving-forward-copy">
        <div class="wrapper">
            <p class="mf-copy no-bpadding">The single best thing we can offer a change agent is a vehicle for bringing your community together to see <i>Most Likely To Succeed</i>. We’ve now been at more than fifty screenings of the film, and seen the power as an entire community gets
                inspired about the possibilities. We have a great team supporting these screenings, along with offerings for a school, a district, and states. Our goal isn’t to make money on this film (all of the funder’s proceeds go to a non-profit helping
                advance U.S. education), but to effect change. And the film, we believe, is the single best film ever done on the past and future of school. Take advantage of it. Oh, for those who ask when the film will be available online, we have turned
                down several offers from the obvious suspects. We feel the real power of the film is when it’s watched in a group setting, and your ability to bring your community together to see the film will vanish if your invitees know they can watch
                it at home (but won’t!).</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="copy-container moving-forward-copy fca-list-container">
        <div class="wrapper">
            <p class="mf-copy">There’s no point in getting a community excited if there’s no follow-on. Our initiative goes beyond the film, with multiple resources that can help your community move forward.</p>
            <p class="mf-copy no-bpadding">Rally your community. Many of us have been in the situation where we fully appreciate the urgency of moving a school forward, but feel surrounded by others satisfied with the status quo. Even to get them to come to a screening of the film
                might be a challenge. If you’re in that situation, one way to begin to build interest for a change process is to share with others some great articles, statistics, or short videos. <a class="black-copy-link" href="/#education-facts">Our website has a few</a>.
                For starters, you might share the following to colleagues involved in your school who might step up:</p>
