    <section class="copy-container moving-forward-copy">
        <div class="wrapper">
            <p class="mf-copy">Your goal is to recruit a core organizing committee to show <i>Most Likely To Succeed</i> in your school. The film has all sorts of accolades, the trailer is inspiring, and audiences love it. By now, some in your community will have heard
                of the film, or even seen it, and they will be your allies. Point people to the film’s website, where they can see a growing list of communities that are screening it. But get your team lined up! Once you have your team in place, we’ll
                make it easy for you to organize a community screening.</p>
            <p class="mf-copy no-bpadding">Once your community has come together to see <i>Most Likely to Succeed</i>, they’ll be receptive -- very receptive -- to doing more. We’d recommend capitalizing on your momentum with a follow-on session. <a href="/moving-forward/for-school-leaders#build-consensus"
                class="black-copy-link">We have developed and used an approach to help your community take on build consensus about the future of your school.</a> This session will energize your community as you converge on a set of desired outcomes and
                design principles for your school. Guaranteed that this will be lightyears ahead of most committee-driven planning processes!</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="copy-container moving-forward-copy fca-email-container">
        <div class="wrapper">
            <p class="mf-copy">Finally, as you work to move your school forward, you’re likely to get pushback. That’s par for the course for a change agent. But whether the resistance comes from a parent, a teacher, a student,or a school leader, we’ve offered some very
                powerful resources on this site that can help them, and your school, move forward.</p>
            <p class="mf-copy no-bpadding">To all of you willing to step up as change agents, you are the heroes of this process, and have our deepest gratitude. Be assured that you’re fighting for the futures of lots of kids and, quite possibly, our collective futures in a country
                that risks being torn apart by a growing divide between the rich and the rest. We have no choice but to fight for the cause of equipping our kids to deal with the innovation era, and supporting our teachers to innovate and inspire.</p>
        </div>
        <p class="mf-copy fca-email-copy">We welcome your involvement and feedback (<a href="mailto:feedback@mltsfilm.org" class="black-copy-link">feedback@mltsfilm.org</a>). We promise to get back to anyone who offers well-thought-out advice or suggestions.</p>
